# рџ”№ 3. Jenkins Pipeline (CI)

Using Jenkins

рџ“„ `Jenkinsfile`

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {

        stage('Clone Code') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/your-repo/ecommerce-app.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean compile'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn test'
            }
        }

        stage('Package') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn package'
            }
        }

        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t ecommerce-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Run Container') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker run -d -p 8080:8080 ecommerce-app'
            }
        }
    }
}
```

